{"title":"Salvation","author":{"name":"Stephen Dunn"},"publishDate":"2013-02-19","lines":[{"line":"Finally, I gave up on obeisance,","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"and refused to welcome","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"either retribution or the tease","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"of sunny days. As for the can’t-be-","stanza":2,"number":4},{"line":"seen, the sum-of-all-details,","stanza":2,"number":5},{"line":"the One—oh, when it came","stanza":2,"number":6},{"line":"to salvation I was only sure","stanza":3,"number":7},{"line":"I needed to be spared","stanza":3,"number":8},{"line":"someone else’s version of it.","stanza":3,"number":9},{"line":"The small prayers I devised","stanza":4,"number":10},{"line":"had in them the hard sounds","stanza":4,"number":11},{"line":"of split and frost.","stanza":4,"number":12},{"line":"I wanted them to speak","stanza":5,"number":13},{"line":"as if it made sense to speak","stanza":5,"number":14},{"line":"to what isn’t there","stanza":5,"number":15},{"line":"in the beaconless dark.","stanza":6,"number":16},{"line":"I wanted them to startle","stanza":6,"number":17},{"line":"by how little they asked.","stanza":6,"number":18}]}